    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application maintains its single-page dashboard structure with three main thematic sections for optimal user experience, now with enhanced visual appeal. 1. **Core Concept**: An initial, engaging section explaining the "3-Layer Brain" model through an interactive diagram. This immediately conveys the report's central idea. 2. **Sales Playbook**: A process-oriented section structured around the sales lifecycle (Approach, Hearing, Closing, etc.). This allows salespeople to find relevant techniques for their immediate tasks. It uses a tabbed interface for easy navigation. 3. **Psychology Toolkit**: A reference section with interactive cards for key psychological principles (Cialdini, biases). This supports non-linear learning and quick look-ups. This structure was chosen to transform the dense report into a practical, task-oriented tool, balancing guided learning (Playbook) with free exploration (Toolkit), which is more effective for adult learners and busy professionals than a linear document. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 1. **3-Layer Brain Model**: Goal: Inform/Engage. Method: Interactive HTML/CSS diagram with subtle hover effects. Interaction: Click to reveal details. Justification: Visually represents the core theory for better retention and engagement. 2. **SPIN Selling**: Goal: Organize/Inform. Method: Interactive accordion within the "Hearing" tab with smoother transitions. Interaction: Click to expand questions. Justification: Breaks down a complex method into digestible steps, improving readability. 3. **Loss Aversion Chart**: Goal: Compare/Impact. Method: Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) with refined colors. Interaction: Hover tooltips. Justification: Visually demonstrates a key bias more powerfully than text alone, now with a cleaner aesthetic. 4. **Psychology Principles**: Goal: Organize/Reference. Method: Interactive HTML flip cards with enhanced animation and styling. Interaction: Hover/Click to reveal details. Justification: Creates a quick, scannable reference library of techniques with an engaging reveal. All choices prioritize interaction and visual learning over static text to make the content more engaging and memorable, now with a more polished look. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
